(PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS SINCE MAY 12, 2022. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since April 12 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since March 12 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRAND WISER was rated between rivals, made a two wide bid leaving the quarter pole, went on even terms leaving the turn and had a long drive to prevail under a drive. ECONOMIC POWER set a pressured pace on the inside and shook clear on the turn, then was headed leaving the turn and stayed on gamely but was outfinished. LAKE NAKURU was void of early speed, came five wide into the lane and was up for the show award. BLOOD MOON pressed the pace three wide and weakened. DEVOTED KITTEN chased the pace four wide and tired. EDICT was well placed on the inside and tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: WINGS OF A SONG set a pressured pace on the inside and made a bid to draw off leaving the turn and then maintained a safe margin to the wire to prove best under a mild drive. WEST ABBOTT was well placed on the inside and faded in the drive, lost show award late. METANOIA was allowed to settle on the inside and lacked a serious rally. WARRIOR'S MISS chased the pace four wide and then was three wide on the backstretch and weakened in the drive. TICK ALERT was settled three to four wide and had no rally. PRIZE DEBATE pressed the winner early three wide and then was empty in the drive. MS KAYS COWGIRL showed little. PEACEMON chased the early pace five wide and stopped. PER RULING FROM THE PENNSYLVANIA RACING COMMISSION, END OF THE RAINBOW WAS DISQUALIFIED FOR POSITIVE TEST.
